communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All communications between Secretary Pompeo and his team and President Francis Ricciardone and his team and executive assistant of the American University in Cairo (AUC) indicating who initiated the contact and the scheduling of the visit to the American University in Cairo, Egypt on January 10, 2019.  Communications with Ehab AbdelRahman (various spellings may be found) of AUC are included in this request.  Note this is the second request for this information beginning May 2021.  Reference F-2021-06176 
Communications were probably via email (AUC's domain is @aucegypt.edu) but might have been via diplomatic pouch, State.gov email, etc.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Dr Thomas DeVere Wolsey

title: Info on Post-Musk-Takeover CBP Advertisements on Twitter/X

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any materials related to the purchase of advertisements for CBP on Twitter (later re-named "X"), after October 1, 2022. This includes, but is not limited to, email communication, written communication, invoices, and receipts.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Philip Eil
